def get_default_features(single=False):
    features = [
     'all-images',
     'omissions',
     'licks',
     'pupil',
     'running',
#      'face_motion_energy', # ignore due to issues with QC
     'hits',
     'misses',
     'false_alarms',
     'correct_rejects',
#      'passive_change', 
#      'beh_model'
     ]
    if single:
        features = ['single-'+feature for feature in features]
    return features

for f, feature in enumerate(features):
    df[feature] = df[feature].abs()


palette = utils.get_experience_level_colors()
fig, ax = plt.subplots(3,4, figsize=(14,8), sharex=True, sharey=False)
ax = ax.ravel()
i = 0 
for c, cell_type in enumerate(cell_types):
    for f, feature in enumerate(features):
    
        ax[i] = sns.pointplot(data=df[(df.cell_type==cell_type)], x='experience_level', y=feature, 
                              hue='experience_level',  hue_order=experience_levels,
                              palette=palette, order=experience_levels, ax=ax[i])
        
        ax[i].get_legend().remove()
        ax[i].set_xlabel('')
        if c == 0: 
            ax[i].set_title(feature)
        if c == 2: 
            ax[i].set_xticklabels(experience_levels, rotation=90)
        if f == 0: 
            ax[i].set_ylabel(cell_type+'\n'+feature)
        i+=1
fig.tight_layout()

In [56]:
df = rspm.copy()
df = df[df.ophys_experiment_id.isin(expts.index.values)]

palette = utils.get_experience_level_colors()

for cell_type in cell_types: 
    print(cell_type)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize=(10,4), sharey=True)
    for i, feature in enumerate(features_to_plot):
        # just matched cells
        data = df[(df.cell_type==cell_type)&(df.cell_specimen_id.isin(cells.cell_specimen_id.unique()))].copy()
        n_matched = len(data.cell_specimen_id.unique())
        print(n_matched, 'matched cells')
        data.loc[:, feature] = data[feature].abs() # get absolute value of dropouts
        ax[i] = sns.pointplot(data=data, x='experience_level', y=feature, #hue='experience_level', 
                             order=experience_levels, color='gray', #hue_order=experience_levels, palette=palette, 
                             join=True, dodge=0.2, ax=ax[i])
        plt.setp([ax[i].get_children()[:5]], alpha=.3);
        if i == len(features_to_plot)-1:
            ax[i].legend(['matched cells'], bbox_to_anchor=(2, 0), fontsize='x-small')

        # all cells
        data = df[(df.cell_type==cell_type)].copy()
        n_total = len(data.cell_specimen_id.unique())
        print(n_total, 'all cells')
        data.loc[:, feature] = data[feature].abs() # get absolute value of dropouts
        ax[i] = sns.pointplot(data=data, x='experience_level', y=feature, hue='experience_level', 
                             order=experience_levels, hue_order=experience_levels, palette=palette, 
                             join=False, ax=ax[i])
        ax[i].get_legend().remove()
        ax[i].set_title(feature)
        ax[i].set_ylabel('')
        ax[i].set_xlabel('')
        ax[i].set_xticklabels(experience_levels, rotation=90)
    ax[0].set_ylabel('\u0394 explained variance')
    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.suptitle(cell_type, x=0.53, y=1.03)

df = rspm.copy()

palette = utils.get_experience_level_colors()

for cell_type in cell_types: 
    print(cell_type)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize=(11,3.5), sharey=False)
    for i, feature in enumerate(features_to_plot):
        # just matched cells
        data = df[(df.cell_type==cell_type)&(df.cell_specimen_id.isin(cells.cell_specimen_id.unique()))].copy()
        n_matched = len(data.cell_specimen_id.unique())
#         print(n_matched, 'matched cells')
        data.loc[:, feature] = data[feature].abs() # get absolute value of dropouts
        ax[i] = sns.pointplot(data=data, x='experience_level', y=feature, #hue='experience_level', 
                             order=experience_levels, color='gray', #hue_order=experience_levels, palette=palette, 
                             join=True, dodge=0.2, ax=ax[i])
        plt.setp([ax[i].get_children()[:5]], alpha=.3);
        if i == len(features_to_plot)-1:
            ax[i].legend(['matched cells'], bbox_to_anchor=(2, 0), fontsize='x-small')

        # all cells
        data = df[(df.cell_type==cell_type)].copy()
        n_total = len(data.cell_specimen_id.unique())
#         print(n_total, 'all cells')
        data.loc[:, feature] = data[feature].abs() # get absolute value of dropouts
        ax[i] = sns.pointplot(data=data, x='experience_level', y=feature, hue='experience_level', 
                             order=experience_levels, hue_order=experience_levels, palette=palette, 
                             join=False, ax=ax[i])
        ax[i].get_legend().remove()
